7/2025-26_Olympic_Sport_Coaches_Show-May_CAOW9.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 13:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59052</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kellogg Announces Signing of Hawa Doumbouya</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/27/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-hawa-doumbouya</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/27/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-hawa-doumbouya</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Hope Coliseum" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/20/1__2_.JPG" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University women's basketball head coach Mark Kellogg has announced the addition of Hawa Doumbouya (Bronx, N.Y. / VCU / Our Lady of Mount Carmel) to a grant-in-aid for the 2026-27 academic year.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/1__2_.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/1__2_.JPG"><media:title>Hope Coliseum</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/1__2_.JPG" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 12:01:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59050</s:story_id></item><item><title>Judis Named Student-Athlete of Week</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/27/track-field-judis-named-student-athlete-of-week</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/27/track-field-judis-named-student-athlete-of-week</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chiara Judis" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handle